        <reg_purpose>
          
    
      <purpose_text>
        <para>Shows the pending status of the IRQ, FIQ, or SError.</para>

      </purpose_text>
      <purpose_text>
        <para>When executing at EL2, EL3, or Secure EL1, when <register_link state="AArch64" id="AArch64-scr_el3.xml">SCR_EL3</register_link>.EEL2 == <binarynumber>0b0</binarynumber>, this shows the pending status of the physical interrupts.</para>

      </purpose_text>
      <purpose_text>
        <para>When executing at Non-secure EL1, or at Secure EL1, when <register_link state="AArch64" id="AArch64-scr_el3.xml">SCR_EL3</register_link>.EEL2 == <binarynumber>0b01</binarynumber>:</para>

      </purpose_text>
      <purpose_text>
        <list type="unordered">
<listitem><content>If the <register_link state="AArch32" id="AArch32-hcr.xml">HCR</register_link>.{IMO,FMO,AMO} bit has a value of 1, the corresponding ISR.{I,F,A} bit shows the pending status of the virtual IRQ, FIQ, or SError.</content>
</listitem><listitem><content>If the <register_link state="AArch32" id="AArch32-hcr.xml">HCR</register_link>.{IMO,FMO,AMO} bit has a value of 0, the corresponding ISR.{I,F,A} bit shows the pending status of the physical IRQ, FIQ, or SError.</content>
</listitem></list>
      </purpose_text>

        </reg_purpose>

